<%- include('header', { title: 'Setup Guide', streamer: typeof streamer !== 'undefined' ? streamer : null }) %>

<h2 style="margin-bottom: 8px;">Setup Guide</h2>
<p style="color: #adadb8; margin-bottom: 24px;">Follow these steps to get the bot running on your Discord server. Takes about 5 minutes.</p>

<div class="step">
  <div class="step-number">1</div>
  <div class="step-content">
    <h3>Log in with Discord</h3>
    <p>Click <strong>"Get Started with Discord"</strong> on the home page. This creates your account using your Discord identity.</p>
    <div class="screenshot">
      <img src="/screenshots/step-1.png" alt="Atleta home page with Get Started with Discord button">
    </div>
    <p>You'll be redirected to Discord to authorize. The bot only reads your username and avatar.</p>
    <div class="screenshot">
      <img src="/screenshots/step-1.1.png" alt="Discord authorization page">
    </div>
    <div class="tip">Click <strong>"Authorize"</strong> to continue. No special permissions are needed — the bot only reads your public profile.</div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="step">
  <div class="step-number">2</div>
  <div class="step-content">
    <h3>Link Your Twitch Account (Optional)</h3>
    <p>From the dashboard, click <strong>"Link Twitch Account"</strong> if you want to enable subscriber role sync for your own channel. This step is optional — you can watch any Twitch channel without linking.</p>
    <div class="screenshot">
      <div class="icon">📸</div>
      <div class="label">Dashboard — "Link Twitch Account" button</div>
      <div>Screenshot coming soon</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="step">
  <div class="step-number">3</div>
  <div class="step-content">
    <h3>Add the Bot to Your Discord Server</h3>
    <p>Click <strong>"+ Add Bot to Server"</strong> from the dashboard. This opens Discord's authorization page in a new tab.</p>
    <div class="screenshot">
      <img src="/screenshots/step-3.png" alt="Dashboard with Add Bot to Server button">
    </div>
    <p>Select which server you want to add the bot to and click <strong>"Continue"</strong>.</p>
    <div class="screenshot">
      <img src="/screenshots/step-3.1.png" alt="Discord — Select a server to add the bot">
    </div>
    <ul>
      <li>You need <strong>Manage Server</strong> permission in the Discord server</li>
      <li>The bot will request permissions to send messages, embed links, and manage roles</li>
      <li>After authorizing, go back to the dashboard</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="step">
  <div class="step-number">4</div>
  <div class="step-content">
    <h3>Claim Your Server</h3>
    <p>After adding the bot, your server will appear under <strong>"Available Servers"</strong> on the dashboard. Click <strong>"Claim"</strong> to link it to your account.</p>
    <div class="screenshot">
      <img src="/screenshots/step-4.png" alt="Dashboard showing Available Servers with Claim button">
    </div>
    <p>Once claimed, you'll see the server settings page where you can configure welcome messages, subscriber role sync, and more.</p>
    <div class="screenshot">
      <img src="/screenshots/step-4.1.png" alt="Server settings page with Twitch Channels and YouTube Channels buttons">
    </div>
    <div class="tip">Each server can only be claimed by one user. If someone else has already set up the bot on that server, you won't see it in the list.</div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="step">
  <div class="step-number">5</div>
  <div class="step-content">
    <h3>Add Twitch Channels to Watch</h3>
    <p>Click the <strong>"Twitch Channels"</strong> button on your server to manage which Twitch streamers you want notifications for.</p>
    <div class="screenshot">
      <img src="/screenshots/step-5.png" alt="Server settings showing Twitch Channels and YouTube Channels buttons">
    </div>
    <p>You'll see the Twitch Channels page. Enter any Twitch username and choose which Discord channels should receive live and clip notifications.</p>
    <div class="screenshot">
      <img src="/screenshots/step-5.1.png" alt="Twitch Channels page — empty state with add form">
    </div>
    <p>Fill in a Twitch username and select the notification channels. You can set different Discord channels for live alerts and clips, or leave one disabled.</p>
    <div class="screenshot">
      <img src="/screenshots/step-5.2.png" alt="Filling in a Twitch username with notification channels selected">
    </div>
    <p>Click <strong>"Add Channel"</strong> and you're done! The channel will appear in your watched list and notifications will start within a minute.</p>
    <div class="screenshot">
      <img src="/screenshots/step-5.3.png" alt="Channel added successfully with watched channels list showing">
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="step">
  <div class="step-number">6</div>
  <div class="step-content">
    <h3>Add YouTube Channels (Optional)</h3>
    <p>Click the <strong>"YouTube Channels"</strong> button on your server settings to add YouTube channels:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Enter a <strong>YouTube Channel ID</strong> (starts with <code>UC</code>). Find any channel ID at <a href="https://commentpicker.com/youtube-channel-id.php" target="_blank">commentpicker.com</a></li>
      <li>Choose separate Discord channels for <strong>video/shorts notifications</strong> and <strong>live notifications</strong></li>
    </ul>
    <div class="screenshot">
      <div class="icon">📸</div>
      <div class="label">YouTube Channels page — Add a YouTube channel form</div>
      <div>Screenshot coming soon</div>
    </div>
    <div class="tip">Video/shorts notifications use the free YouTube RSS feed and don't need an API key. Live detection requires a YouTube Data API key.</div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="step">
  <div class="step-number">7</div>
  <div class="step-content">
    <h3>Configure Welcome Messages (Optional)</h3>
    <p>In your server <strong>"Settings"</strong> page, enable the welcome message feature:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Toggle on <strong>Welcome Messages</strong></li>
      <li>Select which channel to send welcome messages to</li>
      <li>Optionally write a custom welcome message</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="screenshot">
      <img src="/screenshots/step-7.png" alt="Server Settings showing Welcome Message configuration">
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="step">
  <div class="step-number">8</div>
  <div class="step-content">
    <h3>Enable Subscriber Role Sync (Optional)</h3>
    <p>This feature automatically gives a Discord role to your Twitch subscribers:</p>
    <ol style="color: #adadb8; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; padding-left: 20px; margin-top: 6px;">
      <li>First, link your Twitch account and click <strong>"Enable Sub Sync"</strong> from the dashboard — this authorizes the bot to read your subscriber list</li>
    </ol>
    <div class="screenshot">
      <img src="/screenshots/step-8.png" alt="Dashboard showing Enable Sub Sync button">
    </div>

    <ol start="2" style="color: #adadb8; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; padding-left: 20px; margin-top: 6px;">
      <li>In your Discord server, go to <strong>Server Settings &rarr; Roles &rarr; Atleta</strong> and make sure the <strong>Administrator</strong> permission is enabled</li>
    </ol>
    <div class="screenshot">
      <img src="/screenshots/step-8.1.png" alt="Atleta role with Administrator permission enabled">
    </div>

    <ol start="3" style="color: #adadb8; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; padding-left: 20px; margin-top: 6px;">
      <li>Make sure the <strong>Atleta role is above</strong> the subscriber role in the roles list. If it's not, drag it above — the bot can only assign roles lower than its own</li>
    </ol>
    <div class="screenshot">
      <img src="/screenshots/step-8.2.png" alt="Atleta role positioned above Sub Role in the roles list">
    </div>

    <ol start="4" style="color: #adadb8; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; padding-left: 20px; margin-top: 6px;">
      <li>In the Atleta dashboard, go to your server <strong>Settings</strong>, toggle on <strong>Subscriber Role Sync</strong> and select the role</li>
      <li>Your community members type <code>/link</code> in Discord to connect their Twitch account</li>
    </ol>
    <div class="screenshot">
      <img src="/screenshots/step-8.3.png" alt="Discord showing /link command in a channel">
    </div>

    <div class="tip">The bot checks every 10 minutes and assigns or removes the role automatically. Subscribers need to use <code>/link</code> once to connect their Twitch and Discord accounts.</div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="card" style="margin-top: 32px; text-align: center;">
  <h3 style="margin-bottom: 8px;">Ready to get started?</h3>
  <p style="color: #adadb8; margin-bottom: 16px;">The whole setup takes about 5 minutes.</p>
  <a href="/auth/login" class="btn btn-discord" style="font-size: 16px; padding: 12px 24px;">Log in with Discord</a>
</div>

<%- include('footer') %>
